gram \n\n·Growth opportunity \n\n·Daily motivational meetings \n\n·Professional and Energetic atmosphere \n\n·Traveling opportunities \n\nJob Requirements \n\n·Excellent customer service skills \n\n·Must maintain student mentality \n\n·Positive attitude \n\n·Drive to succeed \n\n·Must be able to work well with others \n\n·Leadership skills \n\n·Ability to HAVE FUN \n\nHow to apply \n\nEmail your CV to Collette FAO the management team. Please note, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.\n\n','',NULL,NULL,'0.000','','',NULL,'2016-02-27 11:34:29','2016-02-27 11:34:29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,4,NULL,NULL,0,NULL),(3,1,109,368,'1 Bedroom flat close to Canning Town Station','1-bedroom-flat-close-to-canning-town-station','1 Bedroom flat close to Canning Town Station and all shops and amenities. Part furnished with double glazing and gas central heating. Separate lounge, separate bedroom, shower room and separate kitchen with washing machine, fridge-freezer and gas cooker. Deposit and references required. NO bills are included. £195 per week, £845 per calendar month. Contact Paul : 07850616860\n\n','Newham, London £845.00pm',NULL,NULL,'845.000','07850616860','',NULL,'2016-02-27 10:46:06','2016-02-27 10:46:06',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,4,NULL,NULL,0,NULL),(9,1,183,368,'Red tail shark, gourami, barb, bristlenose pleco','red-tail-shark-gourami-barb-bristlenose-pleco','Changing my tank around and now going for cichlids.\n\nSo all of these have got to go\n\nRed tail shark aprox 3-4 \" \nGourami aprox 3-4 \" \n2 barbs small \nBristlenose pleco aprox 3 \n\n£5 for 1 fish or £15 for everything \nThis is very cheap so stock your tank up a little \n\nPick up sladegreen / Erith \n\n07528811511\n\n','Erith, London',NULL,NULL,'5.000','07528811511','',NULL,'2016-02-27 11:51:39','2016-02-27 11:51:39',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,4,NULL,NULL,0,NULL),(10,1,163,425,'renault clio full mot clean car','renault-clio-full-mot-clean-car','Trip computer, Rear wiper, Drivers airbag, Passenger airbag, Isofix child seat anchor points, Remote central locking, Immobiliser, Electrically adjustable drivers seat, Lumbar support, Front electric windows, Folding rear seats, Sports seats, Alloy wheels, Front fog lights, Body coloured bumpers, Radio/Cassette, Audio remote control, full mot drives perfect no rattles or bangs no swaps or timewasters\n\n','belfast',54.597286,-5.930120,'495.000','07512727570','',NULL,'2016-02-27 11:58:55','2016-02-27 11:58:55',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2016-02-29 10:05:28',1,4,NULL,NULL,1,NULL),(11,1,186,368,'Teach & host international adult and junior students in London - earn up to £770 per week','teach-host-international-adult-and-junior-students-in-london-earn-up-to-770-per-week','Home tuition teachers required to teach school subjects and English and host adult or young learner international students in the Greater London area. You choose when you want to teach and host students making it an ideal job to fit around your existing teaching. \n\nWe require teachers that can teach school subject courses in English (maths, science, GCSEs & A Levels and International Baccalaureate) as well as General English courses. \n\nBucksmore Homelingua was founded in 1979 and since then thousands of students from around the world have studied at the home of one our qualified and friendly teachers. We are British Council accredited for our courses, teaching and operations and we are a member of EnglishUK association of language schools. Due to strong demand, we are looking to increase the number of host teachers. We currently work with over 250 teachers across the UK, including current and former school teachers, ESL teachers and home tutors. \n\nOur English immersion course packages include 10 - 30 hours of tuition, personalised course, accommodation, meals at the teacher\'s house, 2 half day local area excursions and 1 full day excursion for stays of more than one week. The course is held in the teacher\'s home. We also offer short 3-day intensive courses. \n\nOur students come from around the world and study General English, School Subjects (maths, science, GCSE/A Level) and Academic English. \n\nWe always ask teachers first before placing students with them and where possible we match students and teachers based on shared interests and backgrounds. \n\nWhat we offer \n*Competitive weekly teaching fee - adults up to £610 per week and juniors up to £770 per week \n*Training and induction \n*Academic support \n*Director of Studies to assist with planning and academic queries \n*Materials for young learner and exam preparation courses \n*Online webinars and training \n*Training days \n*DBS check for young learner teachers \n*Free online profile on our internet site \n\nWhat you offer \n*A degree in any subject \n*A teaching qualification (CELTA, TESOL, PGCE) \n*Enthusiasm to teach young learner and adult students \n*A positive and friendly attitude \n*Clean and welcoming accommodation \n*Prepared to take students on excursion in the local area \n*Available to host and teach students June - August \n\nRecruitment dates \nApplication deadline: Friday 11 March 2016 \nInterviews: February - April \nInterviews will be conducted via a Skype video call. \n\nOur busiest periods are throughout the summer, half-terms and Christmas & Easter holidays, but we also have a steady flow of students throughout the year. \n\nFor unqualified teachers, a subsidised TESOL course packages maybe available through Oxford International Education Group.\n\n','sweden',60.128162,18.643501,'770.000','02083128075','http://www.flipkart.com/',NULL,'2016-02-27 12:08:06','2016-02-27 12:08:06',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2016-03-01 08:58:00',1,4,NULL,NULL,0,NULL),(12,1,143,368,'Cleaner work available in South West London - Immediate Start - Earn £500 in your first week','cleaner-work-available-in-south-west-london-immediate-start-earn-500-in-your-first-week','Reliable domestic home cleaners required to jo